text: Hey Jamie, sorry you are running into issues. What error are you running into exactly?

I have a reactjs application that I want to persist the source code up into HubSpot to share with another developer.  In the syntax, where I am setting an inline css property like
```style={{ height: '10%' }}```
, the CLI is flagging an error on on the syntax.
The specific error:   Error parsing 'height: 10': syntax error at position 26, encountered ':', expected '}'
